Here's the full performance analysis of `TimeSpanFormatting.cs`:

---

### Scan Execution Checklist

| Recipe | Hits |
|--------|------|
| `.IndexOf(string)` no `StringComparison` | 0 |
| `.Substring(` | 0 |
| `.StartsWith/.EndsWith` no `StringComparison` | 0 |
| `.Contains(string)` no `StringComparison` | 0 |
| `.ToLower()/.ToUpper()` | 0 (but `.ToLowerInvariant()` ×1 — see below) |
| `.Replace(` chains (3+) | 0 |
| `params` | 1 (excluding comment) |
| LINQ `.Select/.Where/.Take/.Aggregate` | 12 live call sites |
| `.Any/.All` | 1 |
| `.ToList()/.ToArray()` | 2 live materializations |
| `new List<` (per-call) | 1 |
| `static readonly Dictionary<` | 0 |
| `new Regex(` | 0 |
| Unsealed non-abstract classes | 1 of 1 |
| Sealed classes | 0 |

---

## Findings

### 1. 🔴 LINQ Allocation Storm on Every `Humanize()` Call (12 sites)

**Impact:** Each `Humanize()` invocation allocates **3–6 enumerator objects + delegate closures**. At millions of calls/min this generates massive Gen0 GC pressure.

**Files:**
- `TimeSpanFormatting.cs:L128` — `.Any()` over `IEnumerable` (enumerator + delegate)
- `TimeSpanFormatting.cs:L140,143,146` — chained `.Where().Take().Where()` (3 enumerators + 2 delegates)
- `TimeSpanFormatting.cs:L149` — `[.. timeParts]` collection expression materializes to new `List`
- `TimeSpanFormatting.cs:L158` — `.Where().ToList()` (enumerator + delegate + list)
- `TimeSpanFormatting.cs:L169,284` — `.Take(Count - 1)` inside `string.Join` (enumerator each)

**Fix:** Replace LINQ chains with `foreach` loops operating over `List<string?>` directly:

```csharp
// IsContainingOnlyNullValue — replace .Any() with loop
private static bool IsContainingOnlyNullValue(List<string?> timeParts)
{
    foreach (var part in timeParts)
        if (part != null) return false;
    return true;
}

// SetPrecisionOfTimeSpan — replace .Where/.Take/.Where with a single loop
private static List<string?> SetPrecisionOfTimeSpan(
    List<string?> timeParts, int precision, bool countEmptyUnits)
{
    var result = new List<string?>(precision);
    int count = 0;
    foreach (var part in timeParts)
    {
        if (count >= precision) break;
        if (countEmptyUnits) count++;
        if (part != null)
        {
